BBK01.WT5012: Exchange rates on the Frankfurt exchange /FRF 100 = DM ... / from January 1960 / France

General: Spot middle rates in Deutsche Mark; difference between buying or selling rate and middle rate in D-Mark: 0.100 up to the end of August 1978 / 0.080 up to the end of 1993 / 0.060 since 1994. Official quotation for NF and FF from the start of 1960 to 30 December 1998 (Previously, between 4 May 1953 and 31 December 1959 quotation for ffrs); see wt5011. Currency conversion with effect from 1 January 1960: ffrs 100 = NF 1 (french New Franc); Currency renamed as of 1 January 1963: FF. From 1 January 1999, irrevocable euro conversion rate: Euro 1 = FF 6.55957. Our specific comments refer to "Frankfurt exchange closed on ..." (Devisenbrse am ... geschlossen) or "Quotation suspended on ..." (Notierung am ... ausgesetzt).
